        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>I. B. Rosenthal &#38; Co.<lb/>
                Importers &#38; Manufacturers&#44;<lb/>
                of<lb/>
                Millinery Goods.<lb/>
                N. E. Cor. Washington Ave. &#38; 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/>
                St. Louis&#44; June 8th 1886<lb/></p>
                    <p>I. B. ROSENTHAL.<lb/>
                M. B. ROSENTHAL.<lb/>
                S. R. LIPSIS.<lb/>
                SIG. ROSENTHAL.<lb/></p>
                
                    <p>Rabbi Dr S. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/></p>
                    <p>Rev Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am one of the Members of the Board in Dr.<lb/> Sonnescheins Congr &#38; one of his many <sic>suporters</sic>.<lb/>  In behalf of truth I approach you to decide&#44; with the<lb/> enclosed oration is or contains anything that is contrary<lb/> to Jewish Doctrines &#38; traditions&#44; some opponents of our<lb/> Doctor in the Board who took hold of this oration openly<lb/> accuse him of having shown by this very words&#44;<lb/> that he is false to the Jews &#38; true Faith of our<lb/> ancestors &#38; that he is not showing by this oration<lb/> full conformity with Israels true teachings.<lb/>  Please answer at your earliest convenience<lb/> &#38; oblige yours most Respectfully<lb/> I B Rosenthal<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
                    <p>June 10&#45;&#45;86<lb/></p>
                    <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Your note reached me this morning&#44; and as you seem to wish for<lb/> an early reply&#44; I hasten to give it this evening&#44; immediately on my return<lb/> home from the Synagogue.  You ask that &#34;in behalf of truth&#34; I shall &#34;decide&#34;<lb/> whether the oration &#34;of the confirmant in your congregation&#45;&#45;a printed copy of which<lb/> you forwarded for my perusal&#45;&#45;&#34;contains anything that is contrary to Jewish doc&#45;<lb/>&#61;trines &#38; traditions&#34;.  I have read it carefully&#44; and found nothing to which I<lb/> could object from a Jewish stand point.  That there is only &#34;One God and one<lb/> humanity&#34; is the teaching <del>imparted</del> we received in the first pages of our Bible; &#34;that all<lb/> will be blessed&#34; &#40;will have a share in the world to come&#41;....&#34;who do what is right in<lb/> the eyes of God and man&#34;&#44; is the <del>doctrine</del> imparting of our Sages; and that Jews are &#34;bound to<lb/> abide by the laws of the nations of which they are a part&#34;&#44; is a principle we derive<lb/> from both prophetism and rabbinism.  But unequivocally as I<lb/> say that &#34;the oration&#34; does not set forth &#34;anything <hi rend="underline">contrary</hi> to Jewish<lb/> doctrines and traditions&#34;&#44; I candidly confess&#44; at the same time&#44; &#34;the spirit of Divine Justice<lb/> and Ethical civilization&#34; is a phrase which may be interpreted in various<lb/> ways&#44; Jewishly and otherwise.  Besides&#44; I may be allowed to add&#44; that the<lb/> occasion on which &#34;the oration&#34; was delivered&#44; <del>demanded</del> called for expressions specifically<lb/> Jewish&#44; so that a child of our people might become &#34;sincerely imbued&#34; with the<lb/> belief that the Decalogue&#44; <del>whose</del> the anniversary of whose <del>was then</del> presentation to our fathers<lb/> was then celebrated&#45;&#45;is the foundation stone of human civilization.  &#34;The confirmant&#34; might<lb/> have been made to confess that the house of Israel&#45;&#45;of whom he should have promised to remain<lb/> a faithful member&#45;&#45;was given the Sinaic Law&#44; to <del>become</del> for ever distin&#45;<lb/>&#45;guished by its observance&#44; as the witness of the existence and fatherhood of<lb/> a creating Lord.  Still&#44; I repeat&#44; the wording of the speech&#44; as submitted to<lb/> me&#44; &#34;in behalf of truth&#34; is not unusual.  These are the views held<lb/> by yours very truly<lb/> S. Morais<lb/></p>
            </body>
